net.sf.jguiraffe.gui.builder.window

Class WindowManagerImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jguiraffe.gui.builder.window.WindowManagerImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WindowManager

    public class WindowManagerImpl
extends Object
implements WindowManager
    A test implementation of the WindowManager interface. This implementation creates WindowImpl objects that have been initialized according to the passed in data. They can be used to test the functionality of the window tags.
    Version:
    $Id: WindowManagerImpl.java 205 2012-01-29 18:29:57Z oheger $
    Author:
    Oliver Heger

      • createWindow

        protected WindowImpl createWindow(WindowBuilderData builderData,
                                  WindowData data,
                                  Window wnd,
                                  String typeName)
        Helper method for creating a (test) window of the specified type. If the passed in window is null, a new window of the specified type will be created. Otherwise the window will be initialized using the passed in data object.
        Parameters:
        builderData - the builder data
        data - the window data
        window - the window to initialize
        typeName - the window's type
        Returns:
        the initialized window
